        .row-fluid
          .span6
            h2 About OpenStreetMap
            p
              h4 Code for America is opening data to make the best map of Macon, ever.
            p
              span When you edit&nbsp;
              a(href='http://www.openstreetmap.org/?lat=32.845&lon=-83.6348&zoom=14&layers=Q') OpenStreetMap
              span &nbsp;you're making a better map for all of us.
            p How do companies catch up to Google and release their own maps?&nbsp;
              a(href="http://arstechnica.com/apple/2012/05/two-months-later-apple-acknowledges-use-of-openstreetmap-in-iphoto/") They use OpenStreetMap.
            p Craigslist is&nbsp;
              a(href="http://idealab.talkingpointsmemo.com/2012/08/craigslist-maps-test-openstreetmap.php") mapping your next apartment
              span &nbsp;on OpenStreetMap.
            p Foursquare uses and edits OpenStreetMap&nbsp;
              a(href="http://foursquare.com") to map places and check-ins worldwide
            p OpenStreetMap is even used to make&nbsp;
              a(href="http://softcities.net/") blankets and "mapkins".
     
          .span6
            h2 Data Tips
            ul
              li(style="padding-bottom:10px;")
                span You can view almost any KML file in Google Maps. Paste the URL into the search bar,&nbsp;
                a(href="https://maps.google.com/maps?q=http:%2F%2Fhistoric-macon.herokuapp.com%2Ftimeline-at.kml%3Fcustomgeo%3D5080a0bf5766800200000346%26r%3D2&hl=en&sll=32.858168,-83.677044&sspn=0.039727,0.074587&t=m&z=14") like this.
              li(style="padding-bottom:10px;")
                span You can download Macon and Bibb County from OpenStreetMap at&nbsp;
                a(href="http://metro.teczno.com/") metro.teczno.com
              li(style="padding-bottom:10px;") When building on top of OpenStreetMap, the data is free, but always give credit.
              li(style="padding-bottom:10px;")
                span The US Census maps the entire US at&nbsp;
                a(href="http://www.census.gov/geo/www/tiger/shp.html") TIGER.
              li(style="padding-bottom:10px;")
                span Make your own maps by downloading&nbsp;
                a(href="http://mapbox.com/tilemill/") TileMill
                span &nbsp;or using&nbsp;
                a(href="http://cloudmade.com/products/style-editor") CloudMade
                span &nbsp;online.

        .row-fluid
          .span6
            a(name="government")
            h2 Government: public data online
            p The map of Macon builds on data from the City of Macon, Bibb County, the Macon Water Authority, the Middle Georgia Regional Commission, and Macon-Bibb Planning and Zoning Commission. In addition to contributing data, governments can also get data back.
            p
              span OpenStreetMap users have mapped historic sites, such as&nbsp;
              a(href="http://wikimania2012.wikimedia.org/wiki/OpenStreetMap_mapping_party") Congressional Cemetery
              span &nbsp;in Washington, DC.
            p
              span The USGS and National Park Service use OpenStreetMap data to build up their national maps.
              ul
                li
                  a(href="http://pubs.usgs.gov/of/2011/1136/") USGS Study
                li
                  a(href="http://www.nps.gov/npmap/decks/choosing-the-right-tool-for-the-job/#1") NPS Presentation

          .span6
            a(name="community")
            h2 Community Groups: 
            p
              a(href="http://maconhabitat.org") Habitat for Humanity in Macon
              span &nbsp;built on the county's building footprints map to show their impact on their neighborhood.
              a(href="http://maconmaps.herokuapp.com/everything.html?table=lynmore&user=mapmeld&lat=32.787338&lng=-83.646888&z=17") View Map
            p
              a(href="http://www.collegehillmacon.com/") The College Hill Alliance
              span &nbsp;mapped housing violations in their neighborhood over the past 15 years. The code is open source, so anyone can make a timeline by drawing their neighborhood on&nbsp;
              a(href="http://maconmaps.herokuapp.com/timeline-maker") this map.
              span OpenStreetMap was the best basemap for the job.
            p
              a(href="http://www.historicmacon.org/") Historic Macon
              span &nbsp;had their historic houses' build dates mapped over OpenStreetMap.&nbsp;
              a(href="http://historic-macon.herokuapp.com/timeline?customgeo=5080a0bf5766800200000346") Timeline-Map

